==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ɛəkɹɑː̩ft/}}
* {{audio|en-us-aircraft.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Etymology===
From ''[[air]]'' + ''[[craft]]''.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|pl=aircraft}}

# A vehicle capable of atmospheric [[flight]] due to interaction with the [[air]], such as [[buoyancy]] or [[lift]].
# {{plural of|aircraft}}

====Usage notes====
* The word ''aircraft'' is a [[Appendix:Glossary#countable|countable]] noun, but with the same plural form as singular; hence "one aircraft", "two aircraft", etc. However, it is becoming more and more common to hear the incorrect usage "aircrafts" among both non-native speakers of English and those who work in the aviation industry.
* vehicles that fly [[ballistic]]ally, propelled solely by [[rocket]]s, are not usually referred to as aircraft, unlike [[rocket plane]]s
* An aircraft with a propulsion system is also termed [[airplane]]/[[aeroplane]].

